The paper deals with face image analysis and proposes a convolutional neural network for face parsing. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of interlinked convolutional neural networks and the focus on integrating local and contextual information suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which could make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
